<title>USA: Carson Pirie sees higher Q3 oper EPS.</title>
<headline>Carson Pirie sees higher Q3 oper EPS.</headline>
<dateline>MILWAUKEE 1996-11-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Carson Pirie Scott &amp; Co said Thursday it expects third quarter earnings, before one-time items, will exceed last year's $0.24 a share.</p>
<p>&quot;Comparable-store sales increased 3.5 percent for the quarter, while total sales increased 7.0 percent, which reflected the company's four new store openings in 1996,&quot; Stanton Bluestone, chairman, said in a statement.</p>
<p>-- Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787</p>
